[b]Casual Carrom (2 or 4 players)[/b]

Carrom for friends — same flow as the tournament game with the strict rules relaxed so nobody loses on a technicality. This is the shared casual rule set every Purist game inherits unless it ships its own (ICF ships the strict tournament rules).

[b]Setup[/b]
• 9 white coins, 9 black coins, and 1 red Queen in the centre
• 2 players (1v1) or 4 players (2v2 — partners sit opposite). A 3-player table fills the empty seat with an AI so it plays as two pairs.
• Two-player games split white vs black.
• Place the striker on your baseline and flick toward the coins.

[b]Turns[/b]
• Pocket a coin you own: you go again.
• Pocket nothing: turn passes to the next player.
• Pocket an opponent's coin: they get credit, your turn ends.

[b]The Queen[/b]
• No covering requirement — pocket the Queen and she's yours.
• No "must pocket own first" rule — you can claim the Queen any time.

[b]Fouls (relaxed)[/b]
• Striker pocketed, or the striker leaves the board: your turn ends and one of your pocketed coins returns to the centre (owed against your next pocket if you have none yet).
• A coin knocked off the board simply returns to the centre — no penalty.
• Miss everything and you're warned; a second miss in a row is a foul — one of your pocketed coins returns to the centre. Touching any coin clears the warning.

[b]Scoring[/b]
• The first player or team to pocket all their coins wins the board.
• Winner scores 1 point per opponent coin remaining on the board.
• Queen bonus: +3 points to whoever pocketed her (no bonus if the winner is already at 22 or more points).
• Match is played to 25 points.

[b]Player Configurations[/b]
• [b]1v1[/b] (2 players) — Each pockets their own colour.
• [b]2v2[/b] (4 players, Teams) — Partners sit opposite. Teammates alternate turns and share a score.
